17:24.310 --> 17:25.608
but it could take up to a week,

17:25.711 --> 17:27.844
so hopefully within one to three
days, I'll feel much better.

17:27.946 --> 17:31.467
Okay. Who'd have ever thought
this is, like, the cure for...

17:31.517 --> 17:34.151
Who'd have ever thought that
it was, like, if you just

17:34.253 --> 17:37.854
put other people's poop
in you, it works? Right?

17:37.957 --> 17:41.491
Morton: <i>While human feces can
transmit many bacterial diseases,</i>

17:41.593 --> 17:43.394
<i>not all the bacteria
that reside in our stool</i>

17:43.462 --> 17:44.728
<i>are bad for our health.</i>

17:44.830 --> 17:46.830
<i>The basic principle behind
the fecal transplant</i>

17:46.933 --> 17:49.266
<i>is that by putting healthy
stool inside an unhealthy gut,</i>

17:49.368 --> 17:51.368
<i>you reintroduce
all the good bacteria</i>

17:51.470 --> 17:52.937
<i>and help restore it to health.</i>

17:53.039 --> 17:54.271
<i>Think of it as a probiotic,</i>

17:54.373 --> 17:56.706
<i>but like a nuclear-level
probiotic.</i>

17:58.377 --> 18:00.877
<i>Dr. Sahil Khanna is Stephanie's
gastroenterologist.</i>

18:00.980 --> 18:04.881
<i>He's performed hundreds of
fecal transplants at Mayo.</i>

18:04.984 --> 18:07.217
What's the, uh, kind of
effectiveness rate

18:07.320 --> 18:09.786
for fecal transplants
to... on C. Diff?

18:09.888 --> 18:13.190
So our effectiveness rate has
been a little over... over 90%.

18:13.292 --> 18:16.327
You say a 90% effectiveness
rate or success rate.

18:16.429 --> 18:18.189
That seems like... that
seems very high to me.

18:18.197 --> 18:19.596
Oh absolutely, it's very high.

18:19.698 --> 18:22.599
There's not a lot of things that
have 90% or higher success rates.

18:22.701 --> 18:25.936
Do you see this, uh, fecal
transplant as being kind of a...

18:26.038 --> 18:27.804
part of a new wave
of medical thinking?

18:27.906 --> 18:30.140
Oh, absolutely.
I think we're in an era

18:30.242 --> 18:32.909
where we are learning so much
about this gut microbiome

18:33.012 --> 18:35.846
that it's going to keep us
busy for the next few decades

18:35.948 --> 18:40.284
trying to figure out how does
this play in health and disease.

18:40.386 --> 18:42.086
Morton: <i>Before the
fecal transplant</i>

18:42.188 --> 18:43.908
<i>was proven highly
effective as medicine,</i>

18:43.956 --> 18:47.257
<i>someone had to take the risk
of using the dirtiest product</i>

18:47.360 --> 18:49.393
<i>of the human body
as a healing implement.</i>

18:49.495 --> 18:51.462
<i>That man was
a Danish-American doctor</i>

18:51.563 --> 18:53.497
<i>from up the road in Duluth.</i>

