and then that goes straight
to them just like that.

23:35.481 --> 23:36.546
Amazing.

23:36.649 --> 23:38.382
Morton: <i>OpenBiome may
know what to look for</i>

23:38.484 --> 23:40.617
<i>in healthy stool donors,
but what exactly makes</i>

23:40.719 --> 23:43.353
<i>their stool healthy is
still a major mystery.</i>

23:43.455 --> 23:45.756
<i>The average person's body
harbors trillions of bacteria,</i>

23:45.857 --> 23:48.759
<i>fungi, viruses and other
microscopic foreign bodies</i>

23:48.860 --> 23:50.960
<i>that make up what scientists
call the microbiome,</i>

23:51.062 --> 23:52.962
<i>and which they are
learning affects not only</i>

23:53.064 --> 23:54.798
<i>our digestion,
but our immune system,</i>

23:54.900 --> 23:57.367
<i>our liver health,
possibly even our mood.</i>

23:57.469 --> 23:59.403
<i>It's practically
its own organ system.</i>

24:00.639 --> 24:03.106
<i>Dr. Rob Knight oversees
the American Gut Project,</i>

24:03.208 --> 24:05.141
<i>which collects samples,
mostly stool,</i>

24:05.243 --> 24:06.810
<i>from volunteers
across the country</i>

24:06.912 --> 24:09.646
<i>and sequences them to
learn what exact bacteria</i>

24:09.748 --> 24:12.182
<i>we're carrying around
and in what proportions.</i>

24:13.285 --> 24:15.285
So the most important
thing with it,

24:15.387 --> 24:16.486
that we've found so far,

24:16.588 --> 24:19.255
is, uh, what happens when you have
C. Diff infections.

24:19.358 --> 24:20.824
So you can see that
these patients are in

24:20.926 --> 24:22.559
- in a totally, totally different region.
- Right.

24:22.661 --> 24:25.495
And then they get this
transplant, and they move

24:25.597 --> 24:27.631
from that bad part of the map
into this good part of the map

24:27.733 --> 24:29.700
where they look relatively
similar to the donor.

24:29.802 --> 24:31.335
So, it's amazingly
transformative.

24:31.437 --> 24:34.404
Morton: <i>Right now there are a
number of clinical trials going on</i>

24:34.506 --> 24:36.640
<i>trying to prove that you can
treat more than just C. Diff</i>

24:36.742 --> 24:37.823
<i>with fecal transplants,</i>

24:37.876 --> 24:39.242
<i>or as they're officially called,</i>

24:39.345 --> 24:41.812
<i>fecal microbiota
transplants or FMT.</i>

24:41.913 --> 24:44.348
<i>While the early findings
of this research</i>

24:44.450 --> 24:46.149
<i>is promising, getting
the FDA's approval</i>

24:46.251 --> 24:50.387
<i>to use FMT for different conditions
is still a long way off.</i>

24:50.489 --> 24:52.956
Dr, Knight: Any substance that
modifies your body's activity

24:53.058 --> 24:54.257
in a way that impacts health,

24:54.360 --> 24:56.960
that is considered
by the FDA to be a drug.

24:57.062 --> 24:59.629
And so by that definition,
a stool is a drug.

24:59.732 --> 25:01.832
And while it's amazingly
effective for C. Diff,

25:01.933 --> 25:03.299
we might be
completely missing out

25:03.402 --> 25:05.669
on all kinds of other things
that it's effective for.

25:05.771 --> 25:07.691
Because we now know that
the microbiome is linked

25:07.706 --> 25:09.973
from everything from
irritable bowel syndrome

25:10.075 --> 25:13.477
to rheumatoid arthritis
to cardiovascular disease

25:13.579 --> 25:15.979
and colon cancer, and
then if the work in mice

25:16.081 --> 25:19.282
turns out to translate to humans,
even things like depression,

25:19.385 --> 25:20.784
autism, Parkinson's.

25:20.886 --> 25:23.553
And so by restricting the
use of stool transplants,

25:23.655 --> 25:25.389
it makes it impossible
to even find out

25:25.491 --> 25:28.392
whether it can be effective for
all of those other diseases.

25:29.795 --> 25:32.916
Morton: <i>Because the early
research has been so promising,</i>

25:32.931 --> 25:34.631
<i>people suffering from
debilitating diseases</i>

25:34.733 --> 25:37.567
<i>have looked to fecal transplants
as a potential treatment.</i>

25:37.669 --> 25:40.670
<i>But as the FDA only allows
doctors to use it for C. Diff,</i>

25:40.773 --> 25:42.506
<i>they feel they've been
left in the lurch</i>

25:42.608 --> 25:44.974
<i>and some have resorted to
sourcing their own feces</i>

25:45.076 --> 25:47.010
<i>and performing the
procedure themselves.</i>

