<i>PJ Ramstack is a Washingtonian</i>

25:49.715 --> 25:51.848
<i>who suffers from severe
ulcerative colitis,</i>

25:51.950 --> 25:54.050
<i>which he treats with
his neighbors feces.</i>

25:54.986 --> 25:56.820
So what I'll do is
I'll take the raw stool,

25:56.922 --> 26:00.424
Mm-hmm. I'm gonna put it
into the Ziploc baggy.

26:04.396 --> 26:05.495
Excuse me.

26:05.597 --> 26:08.164
Yeah. All right,
I think that's good.

26:32.223 --> 26:34.891
I just always put
a little bit onto the...

26:34.993 --> 26:37.193
tube itself, and then...

26:37.295 --> 26:39.863
actually put a little bit
up into the rectal area.

26:39.965 --> 26:42.165
Just to make it
a little bit easier.

26:43.936 --> 26:45.969
Got it in?
Yep.

26:47.072 --> 26:49.405
Some people can
do this really fast.

26:50.709 --> 26:51.908
Just kind of inject it in,

26:52.010 --> 26:55.144
and this will
probably take me...

26:55.246 --> 26:56.746
close to 10 minutes each

26:56.849 --> 26:59.850
to just kind of sit here and
really slowly go through.

27:01.620 --> 27:03.119
How often would you have to...

27:03.221 --> 27:04.955
would you have diarrhea
in like a day?

27:05.056 --> 27:07.290
On bad days,
I'd be in the bathroom

27:07.392 --> 27:10.494
anywhere 15 to 20 times a day.

27:10.596 --> 27:12.295
Prior to starting FMT,

27:12.397 --> 27:15.098
my... the mental side of it, the
anxiety and the depression

27:15.200 --> 27:16.800
were so bad that
I don't think I ever

27:16.902 --> 27:18.334
could have got there with...

27:18.436 --> 27:19.903
Excuse me.
Without FMT.

27:20.005 --> 27:22.338
I don't think that would
have been a possibility.

27:22.440 --> 27:23.740
I would go through these stages

27:23.842 --> 27:26.810
where all, every day,
I'd have suicidal thoughts.

27:26.912 --> 27:29.546
And it was... It just
scared the hell out of me.

27:29.648 --> 27:31.381
That was kind of
rock bottom for me

27:31.483 --> 27:35.418
and that's when I knew I had
to find something for myself.

27:35.521 --> 27:37.854
But, you know,
for me to have seen

27:37.956 --> 27:41.658
such extraordinary results
from fecal transplant

27:41.760 --> 27:44.661
when I saw very little to no
results from anything else,

27:44.763 --> 27:48.097
I feel like in the end,
it's gonna be a big part

27:48.199 --> 27:50.901
of what gets me into remission.

27:51.003 --> 27:53.737
